Class WarcModule

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
Reportable, FormatModule, Parser, Validator, Module
@Persistent
public class WarcModule
extends BaseFormatModule
implements Validator

JHOVE2 WARC module. This class is mostly a JHOVE2 wrapper that uses the JWAT package for the actual WARC validation.

Author:
nicl

processRecord

protected void processRecord(JHOVE2 jhove2,
                             SourceFactory sourceFactory,
                             Source parentSource,
                             org.jwat.warc.WarcRecord record)
                      throws EOFException,
                             IOException,
                             JHOVE2Exception
Process a WARC record. Adds a WarcRecordSource child to the supplied input source. Relevant reportable properties are added to the WarcRecordSource. If there is a payload present in the record, steps are taken to characterize it. The content-type of the payload is established from the record itself or a leading http response. The content-type is added as a presumptive format on the embedded source.

Parameters:
jhove2 - the JHove2 characterization context
sourceFactory - JHove2 source factory
parentSource - WARC source unit
record - WARC record from WARC reader
Throws:
EOFException - if EOF occurs prematurely
IOException - if an IO error occurs while processing
JHOVE2Exception - if a serious problem needs to be reported
